<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Mōri — The Game</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cinzel:wght@400;600;700;900&family=Raleway:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;1,400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="CSS Files/MōriStyle.css">
    <link rel="icon" href="favicon.ico">
</head>
<body>

    
    <header id="WelcomeHeader">
        <h1 class="Animated-Text">Raindrop Studios Presents: <em>Mōri</em></h1>
        <nav id="Directory">
            <ul class="nav-bar">
                <li><a href="index.html" class="button">Home</a></li>
                <li><a href="AboutUs.html" class="button">About Us</a></li>
                <li><a href="Mōri.html" class="button">Mōri</a></li>
                <li><a href="Player-Leaderboard.html" class="button">Leaderboard</a></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>
    </header>

    
    <main id="Mōri-Description">

        <!-- Story Section -->
        <section class="story-section">
            <p class="story-year fade-in">&#x2605; &nbsp; THE YEAR IS 1578, AND JAPAN IS AT WAR &nbsp; &#x2605;</p>
            <div class="story-card fade-in glass-card">
                <p>
                    You are <strong>Mōri Katsuko</strong>, a samurai who has been called by his daimyo to
                    aid the Ikko-Ikki clan at their capital city. Upon your arrival, however, you find the
                    castle has been sieged by the powerful <strong>Oda clan</strong>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <em>Mōri</em> is a <strong>first-person combat game</strong> set within the Sengoku
                    period of Japanese history. It takes inspiration from classic arcade game design while
                    blending modern combat features found in titles such as <em>Chivalry: Medieval Warfare</em>,
                    <em>DOOM</em>, <em>Ghost of Tsushima</em>, <em>Mordhau</em>, <em>Ninja Gaiden</em>,
                    and <em>Ultrakill</em>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <em>Mōri</em> is a <strong>round-based wave survival game</strong> — survive the
                    onslaught of enemy waves and earn money to spend on upgrades and consumables between
                    rounds. The longer you survive, the more of the map opens up to explore and defend.
                    Top survivors earn a spot on our <u>Player Leaderboard</u>, showcasing the ten
                    highest scores.
                </p>
                <p class="story-cta">
                    Will you prevail against the Oda clan's army — or bring shame to your clan and
                    dishonor to your family?
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        
        <div class="inspiration-strip fade-in">
            <p>
                Inspired by &nbsp;
                <span>Chivalry: Medieval Warfare</span> &nbsp;·&nbsp;
                <span>DOOM</span> &nbsp;·&nbsp;
                <span>Ghost of Tsushima</span> &nbsp;·&nbsp;
                <span>Mordhau</span> &nbsp;·&nbsp;
                <span>Ninja Gaiden</span> &nbsp;·&nbsp;
                <span>Ultrakill</span>
            </p>
        </div>

        
        <section class="updates-section">
            <h2 class="section-title fade-in">Recent Updates</h2>
            <div class="updates-grid">
                <div class="update-item fade-in glass-card">Movement speed increased for player and enemy mobs</div>
                <div class="update-item fade-in glass-card">Added a dash mechanic with VFX and SFX</div>
                <div class="update-item fade-in glass-card">Added new combat animations with stylized SFX</div>
                <div class="update-item fade-in glass-card">Added a parry mechanic with its own animation, VFX, and SFX</div>
                <div class="update-item fade-in glass-card">Added a prototype inventory system</div>
                <div class="update-item fade-in glass-card">Added a mini-map with functional enemy and player dots</div>
                <div class="update-item fade-in glass-card">Added an interactive banner used to start and end rounds</div>
                <div class="update-item fade-in glass-card">Added a working in-game and main-menu settings page</div>
                <div class="update-item fade-in glass-card">Updated the main menu</div>
                <div class="update-item fade-in glass-card">Updated the game-over and victory menu screens</div>
            </div>
        </section>

       
        <section class="gallery-section">
            <h2 class="section-title fade-in">Game Snapshots</h2>
            <div class="gallery-grid">
                <div class="gallery-item fade-in" data-caption="Player POV with visible mini-map prototype">
                    <img class="gallery-img" src="Game Photos/Mori.png"
                         alt="Player POV with visible mini-map prototype">
                </div>
                <div class="gallery-item fade-in" data-caption="Tense first-person combat">
                    <img class="gallery-img" src="Game Photos/Mori-1.png"
                         alt="Player engaged in Mōri's tense and strategic combat">
                </div>
                <div class="gallery-item fade-in" data-caption="Main menu">
                    <img class="gallery-img" src="Game Photos/Mori-2.png"
                         alt="Mōri's main menu snapshot">
                </div>
                <div class="gallery-item fade-in" data-caption="Parry mechanic in action">
                    <img class="gallery-img" src="Game Photos/Mori-3.png"
                         alt="Mōri's parry mechanic in use as the player blocks an enemy attack">
                </div>
                <div class="gallery-item fade-in" data-caption="In-game inventory system">
                    <img class="gallery-img" src="Game Photos/Mori-4.png"
                         alt="Mōri's in-game inventory system">
                </div>
                <div class="gallery-item fade-in" data-caption="Interactive mission banner — clear all enemies before the next round begins">
                    <img class="gallery-img" src="Game Photos/Mori-5.png"
                         alt="Mōri's interactive mission banner preventing the player from starting the next round before killing all enemies">
                </div>
                <div class="gallery-item fade-in" data-caption="Dash mechanic in action">
                    <img class="gallery-img" src="Game Photos/Mori-Dash-Edit-Gif.gif"
                         alt="Mōri's dash mechanic as the player sprints toward enemies">
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Poster -->
        <section class="poster-section">
            <h2 class="section-title fade-in">Official Poster</h2>
            <div class="poster-container fade-in">
                <img
                    src="Mori%20Poster.png"
                    alt="Mōri — Official Game Poster"
                    class="poster-img"
                />
            </div>
        </section>

    </main>


    <div id="lightbox" class="lightbox" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-label="Image viewer">
        <button id="lightbox-close" aria-label="Close">&times;</button>
        <div class="lightbox-img-wrap">
            <button id="lightbox-prev" class="lightbox-btn" aria-label="Previous">&#8592;</button>
            <img id="lightbox-img" src="" alt="">
            <button id="lightbox-next" class="lightbox-btn" aria-label="Next">&#8594;</button>
        </div>
        <p id="lightbox-caption"></p>
    </div>

    
    <button id="scroll-top" aria-label="Back to top">&#8679;</button>

    <script src="webFeatureHelp.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
